Description

JOB TITLE – Lab Technician

SHIFT- Per Diem for the weekend either 7pm-7am or 7am-7pm

GENERAL SUMMARY OF DUTIES – Responsible for performing required vital signs and ECG’s on in-patient/out-patient study participants. Also responsible for all blood/urine collection and lab processing.

SUPERVISOR – Clinical Operations Manager

Duties Include, But Are Not Limited To

Responsible for collecting blood samples from study participants per study protocol;
Performing ECG’s and vital signs on all study participants;
Process labs;
Collect Biohazard lab waste and dispose of properly;
Stock lab rooms;
Ship frozen samples according to study protocol;
Receive lab supplies;
Schedule study participates for lab tests;
Check and file lab reports;
Call processing lab companies regarding questions and abnormal lab values;
Attend site initiation meetings;
Other duties as assigned.

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS & ABILITIES – This position requires the following minimal requirements:

Knowledge of current medical terminology to perform a full range of laboratory tests;
Knowledge of laboratory equipment and testing to perform quality control checks and troubleshooting of instrumentation.
Knowledge of medical terminology to communicate with study/medical staff regarding laboratory procedures and results;
Skill in performing a full range of laboratory tests;
Skill in anticipating and reacting calmly to emergency situations;
Skill in developing and maintaining department quality assurance;
Skill in establishing and maintaining effective working relationships with study participants, study staff and management;
Ability to read and understand information about instrumentation in laboratory field;
Ability to follow written protocols;
Ability to work independently;
Ability to communicate clearly, both orally and written.

EDUCATION – Certification as a Medical Technologist (ASCP) or as appropriate for lab service

level preferred

EXPERIENCE – One (1) year experience as a medical technologist preferred.
